@* Integer two-way binding (BENCH n°27): @bind="count" on a text <input>, count an int SIGNAL. Unlike
   string/bool, this PARSES: the change handler mirrors int.TryParse (invariant, NumberStyles.Integer) --
   a regex + int32-range check + revert-on-invalid, so an unparseable entry keeps the field and reverts
   the input. @count (int) renders faithfully as text ("0"/"42"). #set flips it programmatically. *@

<input id="box" @bind="count" />

<span id="echo">@count</span>

<button id="set" @onclick="Set">Set</button>

@code {
    private int count = 0;

    private void Set()
    {
        count = 42;
    }
}
